This paper deals with the discovery of security vulnerabilities in web applications, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves analyzing code snippets and open-source projects, which could be classified under software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). The use of automated techniques to find vulnerabilities could also fall under the category of artificial intelligence and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with specific types of vulnerabilities such as cross-site scripting and SQL injection, which could be classified under the sub-category of security and privacy (cs.SI).
